[
    {
        "id": "basic-crud-flow",
        "type": "tab",
        "label": "Basic CRUD API Example",
        "disabled": false,
        "info": "## Basic CRUD API Example\n\nThis flow demonstrates a complete CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) API for managing products.\n\n### Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | /api/v1/products | List all products |\n| GET | /api/v1/products/:id | Get a single product |\n| POST | /api/v1/products | Create a new product |\n| PUT | /api/v1/products/:id | Update a product |\n| DELETE | /api/v1/products/:id | Delete a product |\n\n### Features Demonstrated\n\n- **api-config**: Centralized configuration for database, API versioning, and OpenAPI metadata\n- **api-server**: HTTP server with OpenAPI spec generation and Swagger UI\n- **api-endpoint**: Individual endpoint definitions with validation schemas\n- **Request validation**: JSON Schema validation for request bodies\n- **Response schemas**: OpenAPI documentation for responses\n\n### Testing\n\n1. Deploy the flow\n2. Access Swagger UI at http://localhost:3200/docs\n3. Test endpoints using curl or the Swagger UI:\n\n```bash\n# List products\ncurl http://localhost:3200/api/v1/products\n\n# Create a product\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:3200/api/v1/products \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"name\": \"Widget\", \"price\": 29.99, \"description\": \"A useful widget\"}'\n\n# Get a product\ncurl http://localhost:3200/api/v1/products/1\n\n# Update a product\ncurl -X PUT http://localhost:3200/api/v1/products/1 \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"name\": \"Super Widget\", \"price\": 39.99}'\n\n# Delete a product\ncurl -X DELETE http://localhost:3200/api/v1/products/1\n```"
    },
